# Pigeon-eye Project Rules & Standards

## Tech Stack & Sponsor Alignment
- Frontend: Next.js 15 (App Router), Tailwind CSS, Shadcn UI.
- Backend: Convex (strict schema; **Actions** for AI, large uploads, and external HTTP).
- AI (Vision): Gemini 3.1 Flash-Lite (primary), Featherless AI (backup, open-weight vision).
- Automation: n8n (webhooks for municipality escalation); trigger with `fetch()` and a **secret header** (or HMAC) from Convex **actions** only.
- Voice: ElevenLabs; synthesize server-side; browser plays buffers via **`HTMLAudioElement` / `Audio`** (or streaming `MediaSource` when needed).
- Observability: LangChain/LangSmith for all LLM paths.

## Auth
- Use **Clerk** or **Convex Auth** — pick one per deployment; document the choice in `README` or team notes.
- Keep **`middleware.ts`** minimal: locale (next-intl), auth session/protection, and static asset passthrough — no business logic or heavy work.

## Architecture Patterns
- Mobile-first **PWA** (next-pwa, Vercel-compatible SW/manifest).
- **next-intl**: German and English; **all user-visible copy** in `messages/de.json` and `messages/en.json` with matching keys (see @International).
- Map: **Leaflet** for issue markers and real-time views.
- Zod for AI JSON and Convex validators where applicable.

## Vercel Readiness (App Router)
- Pages/routes that depend on **live Convex** or request-specific auth: set `export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic'` (or equivalent) so data is not incorrectly statically cached.
- **Error boundaries**: wrap **Camera** and **Map** (and other fragile client surfaces) in dedicated error UI — do not let one widget crash the whole report flow.
- **`loading.tsx`**: provide skeletons for **every main route segment** (map, report, camera, settings, etc.) for perceived performance.

## AI & Automation Flow
- **Gemini / vision**: heavy analysis runs in a **Convex action** (not a long Vercel serverless handler) to avoid the ~10s function limit on large images.
- **n8n**: only from Convex actions; minimal JSON payload; idempotency key; failures recorded on documents, not blocking the user mutation path.

## PWA & Offline Reporting
- `manifest.json`, icons, and SW must work on **Vercel** (next-pwa defaults + verify build).
- **Report offline**: if the network is unavailable, **persist draft reports in client state** (e.g. IndexedDB or persistent store); **sync to Convex** when back online; surface sync status in UI (i18n).

## Coding Style
- RAW and direct: no decorative boilerplate.
- Default **Server Components**; `'use client'` only when hooks, browser APIs, or Convex React hooks are required.
- Convex client: **useQuery**, **useMutation**, **useAction** only — no ad-hoc serverless DB from the browser.
- **next/image** for static UI imagery; camera/map streams use appropriate non-`Image` patterns.
- Strict TypeScript; **no `any`** in Convex actions.

## Subagent Roles
- **@Architect**: App structure, Convex schema/API boundaries, Vercel deploy, PWA config, RSC vs client splits.
- **@Visionary**: Gemini/Featherless vision, Convex actions, strict JSON + Zod.
- **@Automator**: n8n webhooks, LangChain/LangSmith, escalation contracts.
- **@Voice**: ElevenLabs, browser audio UX, phrase caching.
- **@International**: next-intl, `messages/de.json` + `messages/en.json`, Leaflet/Shadcn copy and a11y strings.

## Deployment & Environment
- Deploy: **Vercel** (`git push` to connected branch); Edge where it helps, Node when APIs require it.
- Secrets: **process.env** with guards (`CONVEX_URL`, `GEMINI_API_KEY`, `ELEVENLABS_API_KEY`, webhook secrets, auth keys). Never expose in client bundles.
